-- Lock-in test for the deontic action-type-check fix (checkActionPattern).
--
-- An obligation can be parameterised over the action it requires:
--   GIVEN action IS A Action ... MUST action
-- Here `action` is a *reference* to the GIVEN parameter, not a fresh pattern
-- binder. So the obligation is discharged only by an event whose action equals
-- the supplied one — a non-matching action must leave it pending.
--
-- Before the fix the bare name `action` shadowed the parameter as a fresh binder
-- that matched ANY event, so feeding a different action wrongly FULFILLED the
-- obligation. The globbed test suite never exercised this (the only corpus user,
-- doc/courses/.../module-a2, lives outside the globbed roots), so this file pins
-- the corrected behaviour. It mirrors the `obligation within days` pattern there.

DECLARE Actor  IS ONE OF Alice, Bob
DECLARE Action IS ONE OF doThis, doThat

GIVEN party  IS AN Actor
      action IS AN Action
GIVETH A DEONTIC Actor Action
`obligation to act` MEANS
    PARTY party
    MUST action
    WITHIN 30
    HENCE FULFILLED
    LEST BREACH

-- Obligation: Alice must do `doThis`. A DIFFERENT action must NOT discharge it.
#TRACE (`obligation to act` Alice doThis) AT 0 WITH
  PARTY 5

-- The MATCHING action discharges the obligation.
DOES Alice AT doThat #TRACE (`obligation to act` Alice doThis) AT 0 WITH
  PARTY 5
DOES Alice AT doThis 
